<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idcc6948ae-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70" identifier="/us/usc/t49/s47526"><num value="47526">§ 47526.</num><heading> Limitations for noncomplying airport noise and access restrictions</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Unless the Secretary of Transportation is satisfied that an airport is not imposing an airport noise or access restriction not in compliance with this subchapter, the airport may not—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idcc6948af-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70" identifier="/us/usc/t49/s47526/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> receive money under subchapter I of chapter 471 of this title; or</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idcc6948b0-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70" identifier="/us/usc/t49/s47526/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> impose a passenger facility charge under <ref href="/us/usc/t49/s40117">section 40117 of this title</ref>.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idcc6948b1-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70">(<ref href="/us/pl/103/272/s1/e">Pub. L. 103–272, § 1(e)</ref>, <date date="1994-07-05">July 5, 1994</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/108/1291">108 Stat. 1291</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/112/95/tI/s111/c/2/A/viii">Pub. L. 112–95, title I, § 111(c)(2)(A)(viii)</ref>, <date date="2012-02-14">Feb. 14, 2012</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/126/18">126 Stat. 18</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
